column5: Weather looks good this weekend, never tried fishing in Nov. for bass/walleye.  Packed it in last month after 2 or 3 skunk sessions in a row, have to admit, weather nice - anyone having success these days?
We fish the grand in Caledonia and its been producing. (Not for us, but for others)  Not sure about bass but the steel feed is on.

we fished dunville,lots of piks on the finder but not hitting,york area was slow, i caught two pike .caledonia nothing for me,I was fishing for piks.I think cayuga is the place to be,though i never fished there.Ill bring the boat and see what happens this weekend.
there was a walleye tourny last weekend on the lower grand (dunnville) and lots of walleye were caught.  Go down there and jig near the dam and you will get on them.
